<TITLE> German gets two years for Cambodia child sex abuse </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 PHNOM PENH, April 24 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - A Cambodian court sentenced a 61-year-old German man to two years' jail on Thursday for sexually abusing street girls aged 14 and 15 years, the trial judge said. Jopen Reimund Hubert of Cologne, who was arrested in November during a police raid on a hostel, was also ordered to pay $2,000 in compensation and told he would be deported on completion of his sentence. He lashed out at a Reuters photographer as he was led from the court to a waiting prison van. "I did nothing bad in Cambodia. I saved the lives of Cambodian girls," he told Reuters after the decision, saying he had given them small sums of money to support their families. He also denied police had found images of naked girls on his laptop computer. The deeply impoverished Southeast Asian nation has been trying hard in recent years to rid itself of its reputation as a haven for perverts and paedophiles but with limited success
